cs.LG, cs.NE, cs.AI, cs.SI, cs.RO

The paper proposes a novel architecture that combines Deep Reinforcement Learning (DRL) and Graph Neural Networks (GNN) to solve routing optimization problems. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also deals with optimization problems, which makes cs.SI (Systems and Control) a possible sub-category. Finally, the paper focuses on networking applications, which could lead to cs.RO (Robotics and Control) as a potential sub-category.
